THE ARMORED CAR!

265
00:14:45,458 --> 00:14:48,500
- EH, VASH THE STAMPEDE?

266
00:14:48,583 --> 00:14:51,583
- ( gunshots, laughter )

267
00:14:51,666 --> 00:14:54,083
- YOU'D BE REAL SMART
TO KEEP YOUR DISTANCE!

268
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:56,125
'CAUSE THIS GENTLEMAN HERE
IS NONE OTHER THAN

269
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,375
THE $$60 BILLION MAN...

270
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:01,583
VASH THE STAMPEDE,
THE HUMANOID TYPHOON!

271
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:04,458
- LEAVE HIM ALONE!
IF YOU GET HIM REAL MAD,

272
00:15:04,541 --> 00:15:06,791
HE MAY JUST DECIDE TO BLOW
THIS TOWN TO SMITHEREENS.

273
00:15:06,875 --> 00:15:09,250
- HMMM, HOW PLEASANT.

274
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:11,416
SURE WOULD BE NICE
IF ALL THE TOWNSFOLK

275
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,791
WERE THIS HELPFUL.

276
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:15,125
- UH, EXCUSE ME, MR. VASH?

277
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:17,833
MY NAME IS MERYL STRYFE
AND I'M HERE WITH MY PARTNER

278
00:15:17,916 --> 00:15:20,250
REPRESENTING THE BERNARDELLI
INSURANCE SOCIETY.

279
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,041
AND WE WERE SENT HERE TO--

280
00:15:22,125 --> 00:15:24,166
- HEY, SHUT UP AND
JUST LOAD THE BAGS!

281
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:25,625
- Both: YES SIR!

282
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:28,250
- I FEEL HORRIBLE, MERYL.

283
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:31,083
- IF ONLY I WOULD HAVE
BOUGHT HIM A BOX OF DONUTS.

284
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:33,000
- YOU'D BETTER GET
THE LEAD OUT, LADIES.

285
00:15:33,083 --> 00:15:34,666
- Both:
YES SIR, WE WILL.

286
00:15:39,916 --> 00:15:42,083
- COUNTERMEASURE #1:

287
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,875
TAKE THE PLACE OF A HOSTAGE.

288
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:45,875
( muffled groan )
- WON'T WORK.

289
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:48,041
- #2 THEN:

290
00:15:48,125 --> 00:15:51,416
SEND EVERYBODY INTO A MAD PANIC
BY SHOUTING "EARTHQUAKE!"

291
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,833
YEOW!
- EVEN WORSE.

292
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:56,458
- ( growls ) WELL THEN,
WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST?

293
00:15:56,541 --> 00:15:58,833
- I HAVE TO GO WITH #3:

294
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,166
YOU KNOW, JUST STAND BACK HERE
WHERE IT'S SAFE,

295
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:03,458
LET 'EM TAKE THE MONEY
AND SHUT UP.

296
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:06,541
- I DON'T THINK SO.

297
00:16:06,625 --> 00:16:08,750
- WHY THE HELL ARE YOU
STICKING YOUR NECK OUT?

298
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,875
JUST KEEP QUIET,
YOU JUST MIGHT STAY ALIVE.

299
00:16:10,958 --> 00:16:13,291
AND THERE'LL BE A LOT LESS
DAMAGE AROUND HERE TOO.

300
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:15,250
- LOOK, DO YOU SEE
THAT LITTLE GIRL?

301
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,750
- YEAH.

302
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,291
- HER MOTHER PROMISED TO BUY
HER SOMETHING WITH HER MONEY

303
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,916
THAT USED TO BE IN THE BANK
BEFORE THIS HAPPENED.

304
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,000
- YOU KNOW HER?
- NAH, JUST MADE IT UP.

305
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,958
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING WORRYING
ABOUT OTHER PEOPLE'S MONEY?

306
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:29,916
I MEAN, WHAT GOOD'S
IT GONNA DO YOU?

307
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,958
- NOTHING AT ALL.

308
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:35,791
EXCEPT THAT THIS
SITUATION IS NOT EQUAL.

309
00:16:43,125 --> 00:16:44,458
- Both: HUH?

310
00:16:47,083 --> 00:16:48,750
- HUH?

311
00:16:51,875 --> 00:16:53,208
- WHAT'S HE DOING?

312
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:55,833
- ( whispers ) BIG BRO.
- HMM?

313
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,000
- ( gunshot )

314
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:03,333
- WHAT DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING?

315
00:17:03,416 --> 00:17:05,000
TRYING TO PLAY THE HERO, COWBOY?

316
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:07,958
- NO, NOT REALLY. I'M NOT AS
GREAT AS YOU MIGHT THINK I AM.

317
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:16,750
AW, GEE, THAT'S TOO BAD.
YOU'VE GOT A FLAT TIRE!

318
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,583
WELL, I GUESS YOU WON'T BE
ESCAPING IN THIS.

319
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:21,416
- ( screaming )

320
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,041
- YOU LITTLE--

321
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:26,583
- ( screams, gasps )

322
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:27,791
- ( laughs )

323
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:30,583
HUH? LET--

324
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:33,000
SON OF A--

325
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:36,416
WHOA, LET GO, YOU--
( moaning )

326
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,500
- HOW'D HE DO THAT?
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

327
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:42,416
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHAT YOU'RE
GETTING YOURSELF INTO, MISTER?

328
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,500
THIS GENTLEMAN HERE
IS THE ONE AND ONLY

329
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:47,208
INFAMOUS HUMANOID TYPHOON.

330
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:49,208
HE'S VASH THE STAMPEDE!

331
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,958
- NOW THAT'S FUNNY.

332
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:52,625
PARDON ME.
- ( bones crack )

333
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:55,458
- BUT I UNDER THE IMPRESSION
THAT HE WAS A LOT MORE HANDSOME.

334
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:58,958
- ARE YOU IMPLYING THAT
I AM NOT VASH THE STAMPEDE?!

335
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:01,000
- MAYBE WE SHOULD FIND OUT.

336
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,625
- HUH? UHH.

337
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,208
( thinking )
WHY?

338
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:18,750
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

339
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:21,375
- WE CAN USE FORCE
IF WE HAVE TO.

340
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:22,416
- RIGHT!

341
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,250
- WHY?!

342
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,208
- Bartender:
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!

343
00:18:27,291 --> 00:18:28,708
- HUH?
- HUH?

344
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,625
- ( groans )

345
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:35,250
- ( wind blowing )

346
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:40,666
- ( both gasp )

347
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:43,916
- THIS GUN IS AN ORIGINAL
FRANK MARLON SPECIAL!

348
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,583
AND DON'T THINK I'LL MISS
JUST 'CAUSE I'M A WOMAN!

349
00:18:46,666 --> 00:18:49,833
- AM I SUPPOSED TO BE AFRAID
OF THIS FRANK MARLON?

350
00:18:49,916 --> 00:18:51,541
IT'S A RUSTED PIECE OF CRAP!

351
00:18:51,625 --> 00:18:53,583
YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE YOU'LL
HIT ME WITH THAT THING?

352
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:56,708
- ( sloshes )
WHY?

353
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:00,125
WHY ARE THEY DOING THAT?

354
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:03,750
AND WHY AM I JUST
STANDING HERE?!

355
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:07,125
- THAT THIS SITUATION
IS NOT EQUAL.

356
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:11,041
- HUH? HMM?

357
00:19:14,208 --> 00:19:15,500
WHAT THE--?

358
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:23,708
- UH?

359
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:32,333
- ( laughs ) APPARENTLY
YOU THINK THAT YOU HAVE WON.

360
00:19:32,416 --> 00:19:35,041
YOU THINK WRONG!
- ( cocking )

361
00:19:39,375 --> 00:19:41,208
- A PIECE OF PARTING ADVICE:

362
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:42,750
YOU SHOULD ALWAYS SAVE
YOUR ACES FOR LAST!

363
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:45,416
( cackles )

364
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,625
( gulps )

365
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:50,583
- CHECKMATE, MISTER.

366
00:19:50,666 --> 00:19:52,083
- ( gulps )

367
00:19:52,166 --> 00:19:55,041
- SHOOTING FROM BEHIND'S
JUST NOT MY STYLE.

368
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,125
- YOU'LL PAY FOR THIS!
- ( screaming )

369
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,125
- YOU WILL PAY!
- ( all grunt )

370
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:02,750
- WOW, THEY REALLY
STICK TOGETHER.

371
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,125
HUH?

372
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:07,416
- HMPH, WASN'T EVEN LOADED.

373
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:10,208
- HUH, SURE WASN'T.

374
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:13,208
- ( all cheering )

375
00:20:13,291 --> 00:20:15,666
- HE'S ACTUALLY DUMBER
THAN I THOUGHT.

376
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,083
THAT GUY IS UNBELIEVABLE.

377
00:20:18,208 --> 00:20:20,375
- ( excited chatter )

378
00:20:20,458 --> 00:20:23,250
- HERE'S TO ALL THE GREAT FOLKS
WHO SAVED THE TOWN!

379
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:24,833
IN YOUR EYE!

380
00:20:29,458 --> 00:20:32,666
AHA HA HA!
GRANDMA, WHAT YOU WAITING FOR?

381
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:34,333
FILL 'ER UP!

382
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:37,291
I MEAN, PLEASE FILL 'ER UP,
MISS, IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND?

383
00:20:37,375 --> 00:20:38,458
- THAT'S BETTER!

384
00:20:38,541 --> 00:20:42,166
- ( laughs )
I WILL NEVER UNDERSTAND HIM.

385
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,125
- THINGS TURNED OUT WELL
AFTER ALL.

386
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:45,875
THERE'S NO DAMAGE
TO THE TOWN.

387
00:20:45,958 --> 00:20:48,208
THE CHIEF WILL PROBABLY
GIVE US BOTH PROMOTIONS!

388
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:51,416
- BUT THE BANDIT WAS A FAKE.
IT WASN'T REALLY HIM.

389
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,791
AND WE STILL HAVEN'T
GOTTEN OUR CHANCE

390
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:55,208
TO MEET VASH THE STAMPEDE.

391
00:20:55,291 --> 00:20:57,958
- Milly: BUT SOMEONE
MATCHES HIS DESCRIPTION!

392
00:20:58,041 --> 00:20:59,708
- HUH?

393
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:01,375
- OH MAN, I'VE GOTTA
FIND THE CAN.

394
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:03,416
- Frank: STICK 'EM UP.

395
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,208
- ( laughing )

396
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:14,375
- I WOULDN'T EXACTLY COUNT
ON THIS FOR EVERYDAY USE

397
00:21:14,458 --> 00:21:15,250
IF I WERE YOU.

398
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:17,041
- HUH?
- BUT HERE, TAKE IT.

399
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:20,958
I'VE CHANGED THE CYLINDER
AND HAMMER PARTS FOR YOU,

400
00:21:21,041 --> 00:21:22,166
AND I GAVE IT
A FULL TUNE-UP.

401
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:24,625
- HEY, THANKS.

402
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,500
- AW HECK, YOU DON'T
NEED TO THANK ME.

403
00:21:26,583 --> 00:21:28,958
BUT THERE IS ONE THING
I WANT TO KNOW.

404
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:31,041
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WITH THAT GUN?

405
00:21:32,875 --> 00:21:34,875
- I INTEND TO USE IT
TO CREATE EQUALITY

406
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,291
AND PEACE THROUGHOUT THE WORLD!
- HUH?

407
00:21:42,791 --> 00:21:45,083
WELL, IF YOU EVER
WEAR IT OUT AGAIN,

408
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:47,708
BRING IT BACK,
I'LL FIX IT AS GOOD AS NEW!

409
00:21:47,791 --> 00:21:50,291
- GREAT. AND WHEN I DO, I'LL
BRING THE BOURBON NEXT TIME.

410
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:53,250
- NO THANKS,
I'VE GIVEN UP ALCOHOL.

411
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,708
I'VE GOT BETTER THINGS TO DO
INSTEAD OF DRINKING.

412
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:58,375
- Milly: WHAT DO YOU THINK
THEY'RE TALKING ABOUT?

413
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:00,208
- SHH!
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

414
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:02,750
I JUST REALIZED, PAL,
I NEVER DID GET YOUR NAME.

415
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:05,250
- WELL-- I'M--

416
00:22:06,708 --> 00:22:08,291
( gags )

417
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:11,875
( retching )

418
00:22:11,958 --> 00:22:13,250
- YOU DRINK TOO MUCH!

419
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,791
- Vash: I'M SORRY!
- Frank: DISGUSTING.

420
00:22:17,625 --> 00:22:19,333
- ( animals groaning )

421
00:22:21,083 --> 00:22:22,708
- YOU JUST DON'T WANT TO ADMIT

422
00:22:22,791 --> 00:22:24,875
THAT YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT HIM, DO YOU, MERYL?

423
00:22:24,958 --> 00:22:27,875
- NO, AND I AM NOT FOLLOWING
HIM, FOR YOUR INFORMATION.

424
00:22:27,958 --> 00:22:29,750
WE JUST HAPPEN TO BE GOING
IN THE SAME DIRECTION.

425
00:22:34,708 --> 00:22:36,083
- BANG BANG.

426
00:22:42,875 --> 00:22:44,250
- ( theme music playing )

427
00:22:50,708 --> 00:22:52,791
( singing in Japanese )

428
00:24:13,791 --> 00:24:15,875
- Vash: A PAST THAT
CAN'T BE FORGOTTEN

429
00:24:15,958 --> 00:24:17,375
AND CAN'T BE BURIED.

430
00:24:17,458 --> 00:24:21,291
A PAST THAT CAN'T EVEN BE SHAKEN
FOR JUST A LITTLE TIME.

431
00:24:21,375 --> 00:24:24,750
THE SENTIMENT DEEP INSIDE
EACH OF THEIR HEARTS

432
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:27,916
IS STRONG AND EQUAL.
FOR BELOVED PARENTS,

433
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,250
AND FOR A BELOVED DAUGHTER.

434
00:24:30,333 --> 00:24:33,125
TWO MEN CAN ONLY FIND THE ANSWER
FROM BEHIND THEIR TRIGGERS.

435
00:24:33,208 --> 00:24:36,375
THE MOMENT THE SENTIMENTAL
BULLETS FLEW TOWARDS EACH OTHER,

436
00:24:36,458 --> 00:24:39,541
THE MEN STOOD SILENT,
YET WERE WEEPING.

437
00:24:39,625 --> 00:24:42,125
THE PAST ENSLAVES.

